node.text:
The Word of the Lord says God created man in His own image and called it good. God created a clear, powerful purpose for manhood. Men, true masculinity was built into your DNA. Yet for many people, it has been blurred by conflicting messages from the world around us. We live in a time where men are looking for the codebook to manhood.

At BraveCo Men's Conference, our hope is to answer your hard questions, get in the foxhole with you, restore the narrative of manhood, and release you into the masculinity you were born to carry.

Join us for our first-ever BraveCo Men’s Conference in partnership with Bethel Church, featuring speakers John Eldredge, Kris Vallotton, Brian Johnson, Danny Silk, Jason Vallotton, and Aaron Zint. This is not your typical Men’s Conference, but instead features opportunities to build a brotherhood as well as interactive experiences with professional horse trainer Todd Pierce, who will break a wild horse to demonstrate how Jesus pursues, heals, and becomes one with us as a Father.

Aug 25 - 27, 2021. Register now for in-person and online tickets at bethel.com/braveco

node.text:
BSSM pastors and worship teams want to minister to YOU!

You’re invited to a night exclusively for our local church members, to come worship and encounter the heart of God in a special Encounter Room for the Local Church.

During the school year, BSSM regularly hosts live times of prayer and worship streamed on YouTube for both students and the global BSSM family. These times have been presence-filled and powerful! This summer, they are seeking to create space to bless you. The first BSSM Encounter Room for Local Church in May was incredibly impactful. God loves to fill the room when His children show up in worship!

Worship will be led by Hannah Waters and David Funk, with ministry led by BSSM pastors on June 23rd at 6:30-8:00 PM in the College View Sanctuary. If you’re unable to attend, the event will also be publicly streamed to Youtube so you can watch on BSSM’s Youtube channel! (link in bio)
 
We hope to see you there. You won’t want to miss this beautiful time of worship and encountering the love of Jesus!

node.text:
We received a powerful, prophetic word just days before the lockdown began last year. In a season where planning a new campus for our global movement did not seem to make practical sense, we held on to God’s logic and His perfect timing. This was one of the many words from God that we declared over our church and community last year.  

But it is now a new season. We need to be ready for what’s on the horizon. God has confirmed that we need to build now for what is coming tomorrow. God, give us eyes to see and ears to always recognize Your voice! Let’s declare faith-filled prayers as we step into this new chapter together.

Learn more or make a gift at bethel.com/build

node.text: Today, we're praying for you, that you would find peace, joy, and rest in the always-good and forever-faithful love of God.

node.text:
The Word of the Lord says God created man in His own image and called it good. God created a clear, powerful purpose for manhood. Men, true masculinity was built into your DNA. Yet for many people, it has been blurred by conflicting messages from the world around us. We live in a time where men are looking for the codebook to manhood.

At BraveCo Men's Conference, our hope is to answer your hard questions, get in the foxhole with you, restore the narrative of manhood, and release you into the masculinity you were born to carry.

Join us for our first-ever BraveCo Men’s Conference in partnership with Bethel Church, featuring speakers John Eldredge, Kris Vallotton, Brian Johnson, Danny Silk, Jason Vallotton, and Aaron Zint. This is not your typical Men’s Conference, but instead features opportunities to build a brotherhood as well as interactive experiences with professional horse trainer Todd Pierce, who will break a wild horse to demonstrate how Jesus pursues, heals, and becomes one with us as a Father.

Aug 25 - 27, 2021. Register now for in-person and online tickets at bethel.com/braveco

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bethel Church on July 25, 2021. May be an image of tree and nature.

node.text: "We have this certain hope like a strong, unbreakable anchor holding our souls to God himself. Our anchor of hope is fastened to the mercy seat in the heavenly realm beyond the sacred threshold, and where Jesus, our forerunner, has gone in before us. He is now and forever our royal Priest like Melchizedek." - Hebrews 6:19-20, TPT

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bethel Church on July 24, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'INSTEAD OF REACTING TO WHAT IS, WHAT IF WE RESPONDED TO WHAT SHOULD BE? KRIS KRIS VALLOTTON'.

node.text: "Your kingdom come, Your will be done, on earth as it is in heaven." God, let us be people who pursue Your perspective above all other things. Give us eyes to see as You see and ears to hear as You hear. Teach us how to respond like You would. Lord, we want to be more like You!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bethel Church on July 23, 2021. May be a black-and-white image of one or more people, people playing musical instruments, people standing and indoor.

node.text: "Holy Spirit come, Holy Spirit dwell, fill Your Church with joy overflowing, and peace overflowing, and love overflowing, in all of Your glory, come." - Rita Springer

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bethel Church on July 22, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'YOUR OBEDIENOS TO GOD CREATES COOPERATION WITH HEAVEN.'.

node.text: God calls us to partner with Him in seeing His kingdom come and His will done. This looks like prayer as well as following His lead, recognizing in both the invitation and the responsibility. // This powerful word from Bill Johnson was a part of his sermon on Sunday, July 18! You can watch it on YouTube, Bethel TV, or listen to it on our Sermon of the Week podcast.

node.text: Take a moment to encounter God's presence in this spontaneous worship moment!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bethel Church on July 21, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'JULY 31 3PM PDT SAVE YOUR SEAT BSSM ON-CAMPUS VIRTUAL SCHOOL DAY ATAST A TASTE OF BSSM REDDING'.

node.text:
Have you thought about attending Bethel's School of Supernatural Ministry (BSSM) in Redding, CA, but you haven’t taken the plunge because you aren’t sure if it’s the right fit for you? Maybe you have wondered what attending BSSM could look like…

What kind of teachings would you receive? What do Revival Groups look like? What could it be like to be surrounded by hundreds of students from around the world, united in a culture of faith? We’d love to show you!

We want to invite you to the first-ever BSSM On-Campus Virtual School Day, giving you a taste of a full day where you can come along with us as we take you through a day in the life as a BSSM student on-campus.

You will get to experience worship, hear from Kris Vallotton (Co-Founder of BSSM) and participate in ministry time led by our Revival Group Pastors. You will also get the chance to experience our Revival Groups, where students are broken up into smaller groups that are led by our BSSM Pastors.

We know that by attending the Virtual School Day, you will walk away feeling refreshed and full of hope. It’s not just a day for sharing information—it's a Presence-filled time of experiencing His glory.

Join us by heading to bethel.ws/bssmvirtualdaysignup! While you’re at it, tag a friend who should sign up with you! We cannot wait to see you!
